{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd2a3bf9-8d67-4357-beaf-4df68dc19d87","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's what matters:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL)\n- **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL)\n- **`net462`** — still supported ✅\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET Core side. You'd need to update your target frameworks to something like:\n\n```\nnet6.0;net462\n```\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n- MSTest v3 offers a single **`MSTest`** meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n- There are some API breaking changes (e.g., removed obsolete assertions, stricter lifecycle semantics).\n\n**Bottom line:** You must drop `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` (or replace them with `net6.0`/`net8.0`) before upgrading to MSTest v3.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8749dfe2-d31e-4787-9537-bf86d2370260","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x / MSTest.TestFramework 3.x) made several breaking changes:\n1. **Minimum framework support**: MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2+ and .NET Core 3.1+. Wait, let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 dropped support for:\n   - .NET Framework versions below 4.6.2 (but net462 should be fine)\n   - .NET 5.0 and netcoreapp3.1 are both end-of-life versions that MSTest v3 no longer supports. The framework now requires .NET 6.0 or later for the .NET Core side.\n\nSo the user will definitely run into compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` when upgrading to MSTest v3.","outputTokens":710,"requestId":"5C2F:13E575:4846B7:59BF70:69F5629F"},"id":"c5568b6a-12df-4ab3-8421-9e0c64ee3110","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:34:21.937Z","parentId":"6a462f11-bf31-4d98-bfec